Interface ExactTargetClient

        Throws:
        ExactTargetException - In case of error.

      • sendEmail

        void sendEmail(Email email,
               SubscriberList subscriberList)
        throws ExactTargetException
        This function calls an ET webservice to send an email through ET.
        Parameters:
        email - with ID set to that of the existing email on ExactTarget which is meant to be sent. Further emailclassification(customerkey) can be set.
        subscriberList - The list to which mail will be sent.
        Throws:
        ExactTargetException - In case of error.

      • getAccounts

        java.util.List<Account> getAccounts(FilterPart filter)
                             throws ExactTargetException
        This function returns all the accounts associated with the ExactTarget configuration. If ExactTarget supports multiple accounts for a connection then those accounts can be fetched by implementing this API.
        Parameters:
        filter - Pass null if no filtering needed.
        Returns:
        A list of all Accounts associated with this connection.
        Throws:
        ExactTargetException - in case of errors

      • retrieveDataExtension

        java.util.List<DataExtension> retrieveDataExtension(java.lang.String[] properties,
                                                    FilterPart filter)
                                             throws ExactTargetException
        This function is used to retrieve filtered data extension objects.
        Parameters:
        properties - The properties of the data extension to be retrieved.
        filter - Filter to be applied while retrieving, e.g, IsSendable equals true
        Returns:
        A list of DataExtension objects
        Throws:
        ExactTargetException - in case of errors

      • retrieveDataExtensionFields

        java.util.List<DataExtensionField> retrieveDataExtensionFields(FilterPart filter,
                                                               java.lang.String[] fields)
                                                        throws ExactTargetException
        This function is used to retrieve data extension columns from the data extension specified in the filter
        Parameters:
        filter - Filter should specify the DataExtension whose columns are to be retrieved, e.g., DataExtension.CustomerKey equals *****
        fields - Attributes of the columns, e.g., Name, DefaultValue, etc.
        Returns:
        A list of data extension column fields
        Throws:
        ExactTargetException - in case of errors
